{{Infobox officeholder | name = Nana Otuo Siriboe | office = | order = | image = | imagesize = | alt = | smallimage = <!--If this is specified, "image" should not be.--> | caption = | predecessor = | president = | successor = | footnotes = | signature = | signature_alt = | party = | birthname = | birth_date = <!--{{birth year and age|1956}} or {{Birth date and age|1977|11|04}}--> | birth_place = [[Ghana]] | death_date = | death_place = | restingplace = | restingplacecoordinates = | nationality = [[Ghanaian]] | otherparty = <!--For additional political affiliations--> | spouse = | relations = | children = | residence = | alma_mater = [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology]] | occupation = [[Paramount chief]] | profession = Electrical engineer | cabinet = | committees = | portfolio = Chair, Council of State | blank1 = | data1 = | website = | honorific-prefix = | honorific-suffix = | term_start = | term_end = | religion = | blank2 = | data2 = | blank3 = | data3 = | blank4 = | data4 = | blank5 = | data5 = }}
'''Nana Otuo Siriboe''' is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] traditional ruler, [[Electrical engineering|electrical engineer]] and entrepreneur. He is the [[Omanhene]] of the [[Juaben]]g traditional area. He has served in several capacities in chieftain affairs and held many Government of Ghana appointments.<ref name=":4">{{Cite news|url=http://kasapafmonline.com/2017/02/27/nana-otuo-siriboe-ii-elected-chairman-council-state/|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe II elected Chairman of the Council of State|date=2017-02-27|work=Kasapa102.5FM|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-US}}</ref> He is currently the Chairman of the seventh [[Council of State (Ghana)|Council of State]] of the Fourth Republic.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/nana-otuo-siriboe-chairs-council-of-state.html|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe chairs Council of State – Graphic Online|last=Graphic.com.gh|work=Graphic Online|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dailyguideafrica.com/council-state-elects-chairman/nana-otuo-siriboe-ii/|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe II – Daily Guide Africa|website=dailyguideafrica.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref>
== Early life and education == Nana Otuo Siriboe II was born in the [[Ashanti Region]] of Ghana. He was admitted to study electrical engineering at the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology]] in the 1960s. He graduated in 1969<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rainbowradioonline.com/index.php/general-news/item/7629-nana-otuo-siriboe-elcted-chair-of-council-of-state|title=Rainbow Radio – Nana Otuo Siriboe elcted chair of Council of State|website=www.rainbowradioonline.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref> and after a brief stint as an engineer was installed as the paramount chief of the Juabeng traditional area.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/news/appointment-otuo-siriboe-is-the-new-chairman-of-council-of-state-id6291911.html|title=Appointment: Otuo Siriboe is the new chairman of Council of State|last=Adu|first=Alice|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-US}}</ref>
== Enstoolment and rule == Nana Otu Siriboe II was installed as [[Paramount chief|Paramount Chief]] of Juabeng Traditional area in 1971. He has the official title of Juabenghene – Chief of Juabeng.<ref name=":0" /> While serving as a traditional ruler, he has acquired vast experience in the fields of business, governance and chieftain affairs in the ensuing years after his installment.<ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=http://citifmonline.com/2017/02/28/council-of-state-elects-nana-otuo-siriboe-ii-as-chairman/|title=Council of State elects Nana Otuo Siriboe II as Chairman – Ghana News|date=2017-02-28|work=Ghana News|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-US}}</ref> Nana Siriboe II performs several assignments with and for the [[Asantehene]] and the Asante Kingdom. In February, 2017, he accompanied the Asantehene, Osei Tutu II, to [[Seychelles]], where they met the [[President of Seychelles]], [[James Michel]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gbcghana.com/1.3272990|title=Asantehene rounds off visit to Seychelles|last=Adjorlolo|first=Ruth Abla|work=gbcghana.com|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref>
== Council of State == During the [[John Agyekum Kufour]] administration, Nana Siriboe II was appointed to the council of state. He served two terms as a member of the council from 2001 to 2009.<ref name=":2" /> In February 2017 he was again appointed to the council by President [[Nana Akufo-Addo|Nana Akuffo-Addo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ghanabusinessnews.com/2017/03/01/nana-siriboe-ii-is-council-of-state-chairman/|title=Nana Siriboe II is Council of State Chairman – Ghana Business News|date=2017-03-01|work=Ghana Business News|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://presidency.gov.gh/index.php/2017/02/14/composition-of-the-council-of-state/|title=Composition of The Council Of State – The Presidency, Republic of Ghana|website=presidency.gov.gh|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref> During the swearing-in ceremony held at The Flagstaff House, President Akuffo-Addo entreated the council to advise him well with the view to always propel Ghana to greater heights.<ref name=":3" /> He was unanimously elected to chair all the activities of the twenty five member council.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.modernghana.com/news/758170/council-of-state-elects-juabenhene-nana-otuo-siriboe-ii-as-c.html|title=Council of State elects Juabenhene Nana Otuo Siriboe II as Chairman|work=Modern Ghana|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-gb}}</ref> During the handing-over ceremony of the sixth session of the council to the seventh, the outgoing council chair, [[John S. Nabila|Naa Prof. John S. Nabila]], advised the new house to give their best counsel to the new government to ensure that the country and all its citizens would live in prosperity and peace.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/local/social/201702/307237.php?storyid=100&|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe II Elected Chairman of the Council of State|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2017-12-14}}</ref> Nana Siriboe's responsibilities as the chair of the council include meeting with Ghanaian of all political persuasions and professionals to listen to their concern and views so an unbiased conclusion can be attained during the council's deliberations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://therepublicnewsonline.com/nana-otuo-siriboe-ii-challenged/|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe II Challenged|date=2017-05-31|work=The Republic|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.todaygh.com/nana-otuo-siriboe-elected-ccil-state-chair/|title=Nana Otuo Siriboe elected C’cil of State chair – Today Newspaper|date=2017-02-28|work=Today Newspaper|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-US}}</ref> He regularly makes public statements which held to shape both government and private industry policies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanamma.com/2017/08/14/government-must-be-strict-in-regulating-industrial-sector-nana-otuo-siriboe-ii/|title=Government must be strict in regulating industrial sector – Nana Otuo Siriboe II|website=www.ghanamma.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref> Six months after becoming chair of the Council of State, Nana Otu Siriboe II, in an address enumerated some of the work the council had done. They included 36 meetings to discuss important issues concerning the country. Chief among the issues according to him were those that concerned the creation of new regions in the country.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ghanacrusader.com/council-of-state-met-36-times-on-creation-of-new-regions-nana-otuo-siriboe-ii/|title=Council of State met 36 times on new Regions – Nana Otuo Siriboe II|date=2017-08-16|work=GhanaCrusader.com – Latest News in Ghana and Beyond|access-date=2017-12-12|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/news/3917-creation-of-new-administrative-regions-council-of-state-recommends-commission-of-enquiry|title=CREATION OF NEW ADMINISTRATIVE REGIONS—COUNCIL OF STATE RECOMMENDS COMMISSION OF ENQUIRY – Government of Ghana|website=www.ghana.gov.gh|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-12-12}}</ref>
== Positions held == Throughout his life as an electrical engineer and traditional ruler, Nana Siriboe II has held several positions in public life.<ref name=":1" /> The time frame for this has been over forty six years and they include:<ref name=":1" /> * Member of Constituent Assembly of 1979<ref name=":4" /> * Member of [[Ghana Broadcasting Corporation]] Board<ref name=":4" /> * [[Komfo Anokye Teaching Hospital]] Board<ref name=":4" /> * [[St. Louis Senior High School|St. Louis Secondary School]] Board<ref name=":4" /> * Chairman of the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology|KNUST]] Council<ref name=":4" /> * Member of Lands Commission<ref name=":0" /> * Member of [[Ghana Prisons Service|Ghana Prison Service]] Council<ref name=":4" /> * Ghana Trade Fair Authority<ref name=":4" /> * Director of [[AngloGold Ashanti|Anglogold Ashanti]]<ref name=":4" /> * Member Council of State<ref name=":4" /> * Chairman Council of State<ref name=":4" />
